title: Hit the Road for Our Future

address_lines: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
location.venue: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details

description:
**Join Us for a Visibility Event to Defend Democracy**  

Our democracy thrives when we show up — and that doesn’t always mean thousands in the streets. Sometimes, presence alone makes the difference.  

We invite you to join us in a peaceful and powerful **visibility event** where we will stand together — literally — on safe walk bridges and highway overpasses throughout Akron. With bold, high-visibility signs like **NO KINGS** and **HANDS OFF** and **HIT THE ROAD TRUMP** we’ll remind passing drivers that democracy is worth fighting for.  

This is an **anti-Trump, anti-Project 2025, pro-democracy event**. We believe in safeguarding the Constitution and resisting efforts to undermine it. **Every voice counts. Every presence matters.** Whether you’re alone or in a group, your participation sends a message: We will not be silent.  

🔹 **Bring a sign** with a short, clear message. Make it bold, make it visible.  
🔹 **Stand with us** whether for a few minutes or an hour.  
🔹 **Be seen, be heard, be part of something meaningful.**  

Change begins with visibility. Let’s stand together for democracy.
accessibility_notes: This visibility event is probably not ideal for someone with mobility issues. Parking will be in a nearby neighborhood, and there will be a short walk to the overpass.

title: L.A. Trump Must Go Now! Protest - Rally and March
description:
Take to the streets on May 17 in mass protests to make Trump Must Go NOW! known in cities and towns. These protests combined with dramatic banner drops, vigils, and other creative nonviolent actions across the country in the days going into Saturday, on the day itself, and in the days after can make get this demand seen by millions:

We all feel it – the atrocities are relentless. Another right snatched away. Someone else disappeared. Due process shredded. Law firms targeted. Universities threatened. Books banned. Immigrants shipped to overseas forever-prisons. Trump promises to disappear “home-growns” (US citizens) next. Trans people banned from the military. It feels impossible to keep up.

We cannot win by chasing each attack as it comes, overwhelmed and outmatched by the vicious speed of Trump's fascist regime. Nor can we wait until 2026 or 2028.

But there is a way to win – a way to defeat this fascist juggernaut.

It is time to come together to take the offense against the whole damn thing — infusing “TRUMP MUST GO NOW!” into all the resistance movements forging a mighty force to stop the regime from carrying out its horrific fascist assault on people here and around the world.

The Refuse Fascism Call to Conscience/Call to Act breaks down the strategy to oust this regime through mass, sustained, nonviolent protest and resistance. Read it. Sign it at RefuseFascism.org/act Spread it to others.

Then, On May 17, join with others across this country to make a big leap in projecting this demand – Trump Must Go Now! – to the tens of millions who are heartsick and furious about all Trump is doing. Let them see there is a movement for them to join with a real strategy to win. Keep raising this demand all summer long, including at the nationwide protests called for June 14,“No Kings Day”!

If we act with courage and heart, if we unite all who can be united from diverse political perspectives, we have the numbers and the power to reclaim the future.

In the Name of Humanity, We Refuse to Accept A Fascist America!

description:
This national call to action coincides with our local 100th consecutive day of protesting in Tribou Park.

We know it is not the number of days that count- but the number of reasons we have to keep coming out that do.    Bring your reasons, and come join us!

There will be sign holding, waving, postcard writing, chanting, community spirit building , mass call to congress, group art project and more!!!

title: 100th day of Protest!  Call for community solidarity!
description:
Join us in Woodstock, Vt- where we have been holding an ongoing daily protest from 12-1pm in Tribou Park since Feb 7th.

Sat. May 17 will be our 100th day of protesting and we would love for you to stand with us in solidarity!  We know the number of days is not the important thing- but the reasons we all have to stop Trump that are important.  These are the things we care about most, and out of love are committed to standing up for to save.   So many things are at stake.  We need to build our people power and show up for each other during this trying time.

Bring a sign or borrow one of ours.  
We will have a group art project, postcard writing, sign holding and waving to passerby’s, cookies, and more!  This is a peaceful protest, desiring to make resistance visible- but also desiring to meet new and like minded people, and encourage each other in knowing we are not alone.

Outside- Rain or Shine. 
Dress for the weather.

Street Parking available. Some is metered.  Or free parking in health center lot or east end park.

title: Veterans Defend the Constitution

address_lines: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
location.venue: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details

description:
Join us as we celebrate and support the voices of Veterans!

America made a promise to its veterans. It's a promise we intend to keep.

On June 6th, join thousands of veterans, military families, and their allies on the National Mall in Washington, D.C., for the Unite for Veterans, Unite for America Rally.

We are coming together to defend the benefits, jobs, and dignity that every generation of veterans has earned through sacrifice.

Veteran jobs, healthcare, and essential VA services are under attack. We will not stand by.

Veterans and military family members are being fired by the thousands from federal jobs. Our healthcare is being gutted. Our benefits are under siege.

This isn't the first time veterans have had to fight for what was promised. From the Bonus Army of 1932 to the battles for the GI Bill and Agent Orange care, veterans have always led the charge for justice.

Now, it's our turn.

We rally to:

Defend veteran and military family member employment in the federal workforce

Stop the privatization and weakening of the Department of Veterans Affairs

Hold political leaders accountable for policies that harm veterans and their families

title: OSOS Community Listening Session: San Antonio
description:
✊🏽 The fight didn’t end with the voucher vote. It’s just beginning.

Join Our Students, Our Schools x San Antonio Alliance for a powerful community listening session about the future of public education in San Antonio.

This isn't just a space to vent—it's a space to vision, build, and organize. Together, we’ll name the harms, share our stories, and build a path forward to protect and invest in public schools.

Hear directly from local educators, parents, and students. Learn how recent voucher laws and school closures are impacting our communities. And find out how you can get involved in local organizing, board meetings, and advocacy efforts.

Let’s show up for each other—and build something bold, together.

🗣️ This session includes:

Lived experiences from SAISD students, educators, and parents

A deeper look at what voucher laws mean for San Antonio

Tools for community action and organizing

A call to action rooted in justice and collective power

title: New Tampa Dems - Partisan Voter Registration and Postcarding

address_lines: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
location.venue: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details

description:
Come join us at the New Tampa Regional Library for PARTISAN voter registration (via text message) and postcarding, in coordination with Field Team 6. 

We are ONLY registering Democrats and left-leaning independents/NPA. We'll show you how this is done when you come to the event.

Field Team 6 is the national leader in partisan voter registration, using a first-of-its-kind database to reach out via email, text, and postcard to register Democrats in the most flippable states and districts nationwide, where Democrats are needed most. 

We'll provide training on how to conduct the voter registration efforts via text (bring your own phone) and postcarding. If you've used the virtual phone bank (VPB) before, you will be using the same interface. An ActionID will be required (we can show you how to get this), and a Google Voice number is recommended (but not required).

title: 100% Clean Electricity Lobby Day

sponsor.name: New Jersey League of Conservation Voters

description:
Governor Murphy has committed to a 100% clean electricity future by 2035 through executive order. But unless this goal is passed by legislation, it could be delayed or eliminated entirely. 

Because the federal administration is moving full speed towards a grid powered by dirty energy, it is up to states to take action on climate change while we still can. And for this bill, we are running out of time. 

Join us at 9am on June 12th at the Trenton State House Annex Building front steps to urge our leaders to pass this crucial legislation. If you want a cleaner and cheaper energy future for New Jersey that is free of dirty fossil fuels, we need your voice! Following this rally and media moment, join us for a day of action lobbying your own legislators - now is the time to make your voice heard. 

Sign up for more details.

title: Glen Cove, NY: Tell Assemblymember Lavine: Pass NY HEAT!
description:
Join us for a rally outside Assemblymember Chuck Lavine's office to urge him to fight for clean and affordable energy by co-sponsoring and helping pass the NY HEAT Act.

**With the state budget finally done, Albany lawmakers must prioritize passing the NY HEAT Act in the waning weeks of the legislative session.**

New Yorkers are being crushed by unaffordable utility bills, and the NY HEAT Act is the solution we need — but Assembly Speaker Carl Heastie and legislative leadership are dragging their feet to put it to a vote.

The Senate has passed NY HEAT two years in a row. The Assembly must stop siding with fossil fuel interests and get it done this year!

The NY HEAT Act is our top climate priority, with its promise of lower energy bills while eliminating massive subsidies to the fracked gas industry.

As New Yorkers face the threats of climate change and rising costs of living, the NY HEAT Act will make energy more affordable while moving off fossil fuels.

_Rally co-sponsors: All Our Energy, Food & Water Watch, Long Island Progressive Coalition (list in formation)_

Join us for the monthly meeting of the KFTC Jefferson County Public School Strong team. 

The Public School Strong Kentucky team is made up of parents, students, educators and community members who are committed to honest, equitable and fully funded public schools. We support each other in turning out to local school board meetings to observe, make our Public School Strong movement visible, and speak up to promote, protect and strengthen our public education system. title: Ukraine - Past, Present, and Future
description:
Please join us as we discuss past, current, and likely future events in Ukraine, and ways we may be able to help them through the current crisis.

We have many Ukrainian neighbors, with relatives who still experience the horror of the current war. I feel an obligation to learn all I can and how best I can help.  I hope you do, too! State Representative Eric Ager, a former diplomat, will be our guest speaker. Eric has served as a Democratic member of the North Carolina House of Representatives from the 114th district since 2023. He is well acquainted with the political turmoil in that region. 
We hope to also have attendance from AVL4Ukraine, a local support group.

Who should attend:  Everyone concerned about the war in Ukraine are invited to attend.
